Text.Value: |Wait, I've been through your bag several times and not seen it.|
|So I'd be immortal if I cast this scroll?|
|Alright, keep your secrets.|
|'Last Resort?' Should I...or Baldur's Gate...be worried?|
|Thank you. When I know you better, I'll talk about it.|
|It's not a safe one to cast.|
|But it won't hurt anyone, I'll tell you that.|
|I don't want to talk about this scroll|
|So at great cost to my powers, I put it onto a scroll. Just to give me the choice.|
|Oh definitely. I've secretly converted to the Shadow Druids and now I plan to blow up the city.|
|It was. I've a fraction of my power in my prime. Made worse because that one failed.|
|Can I cast THAT one?|
|Why would I keep personal effects in my bag?|
|Oh, absolutely. But not because any of you are in danger.|
|Well, well, well. Looks like an interesting scroll you have there.|
|Cast it? That faulty thing? No, I wouldn't do that.|
|Just know that one's a failed one.|
|Spoilsport.|
|What? No. Stop trying to cast my scrolls.|
|I keep the real one here with me at all times.|
|...Which is also why it isn't on me either, but thanks for not lunging at me to get it.|

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: It was pointed out to me that if it's on her, it would be pickpocketable. So this is my handwave while trying to maintain the narrative beat of it. There are certainly better ways to do this...

Text.Value: |Tell you what, next time you get a super secret special scroll, I'll pester you about that one hm?|
|You might know this already, but druids like myself eventually slow down their ageing. I'm not so sure I want that.|
|Can't I just cast it and find out what it is?|
|Please. Not everything is about Baldur's Gate.|
|Let's talk more about it in my default dialogue.|
|It's an important scroll. I'm not chancing it falling into the wrong hands.|
|That sounds harrowing.|
|Plotting BG's downfall?|
|Let's just say...it's something I need to think on.|
|Weird, but ok. We can talk about it in my default dialogue if you change your mind.|

Synopsis:
Player has found Jaheira's scroll (marked 'Last Resort') in the basement of her house.

Mainly this is here to open up the fact that Jaheira has something deeper you need to talk about and give you the follow up in her default dialogue
